race.comment: The well-related AMUSEANTES (8) (half to G1 winner Startantes) returned in fine fashion with a strong win over this track and trip before just running into one better at Eagle Farm last time out. Looks the runner in this field with the most upside and should be right there at the business end. SULTRY SIREN (5) also hails from a handy family (half to 2xG1 winner Shadow Hero) and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Is a three-time winner here who can make her presence felt. HERMANITA (3) is three from three over this course and distance and gets some weight off with the 2kg claim. Top-three candidate. CHEVAL CHIC (9) has a good second-up record with two wins and two seconds from five starts. Has to be included. FLYING DESTINY (2) best of the rest while fresh.
